[src:guided-decoding/context-free-grammar] A language L is said to be a context-free language (CFL), if there exists a CFG G, such that $L=L(G)$ .
[src:guided-decoding/context-free-grammar] Non-deterministic pushdown automata recognize exactly the context-free languages.
